[
    {
        "content": "<p>Regarding this page: <a href=\"http://hapifhir.io/doc_rest_operations.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hapifhir.io/doc_rest_operations.html\">http://hapifhir.io/doc_rest_operations.html</a><br>\nThere is a statement under \"Setting Tags in a Create/Update method\" which states: \"Note that FHIR specifies that in an update method, any tags supplied by the client are copied to the newly saved version, as well as any tags the existing version had.\"<br>\nI believe this is incorrect. <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191404\">@John Moehrke</span> can you confirm?</p>",
        "id": 162071641,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553883881
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also found this:<br>\n<a href=\"http://hapifhir.io/doc_tags.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hapifhir.io/doc_tags.html\">http://hapifhir.io/doc_tags.html</a><br>\nWhich has a broken link to <a href=\"http://www.hl7.org/implement/standards/fhir/extras.html#tag\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://www.hl7.org/implement/standards/fhir/extras.html#tag\">http://www.hl7.org/implement/standards/fhir/extras.html#tag</a><br>\nWas hopeful I would find some answers there... then the cursed broken link</p>",
        "id": 162072450,
        "sender_full_name": "Sean McIlvenna",
        "timestamp": 1553884442
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the tags should be no different than any other element. Where in the FHIR spec is this stated? As anywhere this is said needs to be corrected.   There are some cases where policy may declare that a change in only the tag is not a change in the lastUpdated, but that is a policy not a mandate.</p>",
        "id": 162072826,
        "sender_full_name": "John Moehrke",
        "timestamp": 1553884683
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the correct link is <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#simple-tags\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#simple-tags\">http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#simple-tags</a></p>",
        "id": 162076310,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1553887159
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and, in particular, with regard to this question: <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#tag-updates\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#tag-updates\">http://hl7.org/fhir/resource.html#tag-updates</a></p>",
        "id": 162076344,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1553887191
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so then, how does one indicate that they want to replace the security tags with new ones?  This is mentioned as the final \"However...\" sentence</p>",
        "id": 162076862,
        "sender_full_name": "John Moehrke",
        "timestamp": 1553887659
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-add.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-add.html\">http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-add.html</a> and <a href=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-delete.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-delete.html\">http://hl7.org/fhir/resource-operation-meta-delete.html</a></p>",
        "id": 162077511,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1553888219
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so those operations are for meta... which is fine and interesting. I am more concerned about the tag-update rules that have special handling for security tags. If all of meta was handled the same way, then it would be more clear.</p>",
        "id": 162077797,
        "sender_full_name": "John Moehrke",
        "timestamp": 1553888433
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>all of meta is special. the rules are different for different elements in meta</p>",
        "id": 162077843,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1553888484
